West African Industrial Production Declines in Fourth Quarter

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-04-28T17:45:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/west-african-industrial-production-declines-in-fourth-quarter.html
Industrial production in the eight-
nation West African Economic and Monetary Union declined 5.4
percent in the fourth quarter of 2010 as oil refining and
extraction declined, the region’s central bank said.  Output in agriculture rose 8.3 percent in the period, the
Dakar-based Central Bank of West African States said in an e-
mailed statement today.  Cotton production grew 25 percent, while output of peanuts
rose 3.5 percent, according to the statement, which didn’t
provide specific production figures.  The union includes the states of Togo,  Burkina Faso ,
Senegal,  Ivory Coast , Mali, Niger, Guinea-Bissau and Benin,
which all the common CFA franc currency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 